Detailed Description

template<class Value, class HashFunction = hash<Value>, class KeyEqual = std::equal_to<Value>, class DiscardFunction = CacheSetDiscardIgnore< Value >, class Allocator = std::allocator<Value>>
class mm::cache_set< Value, HashFunction, KeyEqual, DiscardFunction, Allocator >

CacheSet class.

Implements a set container like std::hash_set, but with a fixed element number.

Template Parameters

  • Value : The type of items contained in the set.
  • HashFunction : Callable hasher.
  • DiscardFunction : Discarded item manager.
  • Allocator : Allocator to be used.

template<class Value, class HashFunction = hash<Value>, class KeyEqual = std::equal_to<Value>, class DiscardFunction = CacheSetDiscardIgnore< Value >, class Allocator = std::allocator<Value>>
pair<iterator,bool> mm::cache_set< Value, HashFunction, KeyEqual, DiscardFunction, Allocator >::insert ( const value_type &  obj  )  [inline]

Insert an item in the set.

The item, the pair(key, data), will be inserted in the hash table. In case of a key hash collision, the inserted item will replace the existing one.

Following the DiscardFunction policy there will be a notification that old item has been replaced.

Returns:
A pair<iterator,bool> which contain an iterator to the inserted item and true if the item was correctly inserted, or false if the item was not inserted.
